
# characters encoding in raw messages

example:
```
=C3=A8	-	C3 A8	-	Ã¨
```

----


# search

https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topicsearchin/spaghettiopendata/{options}/{group_path}/{topic_path}

where {options} is a list of the following (not yet complete)

before:YYYY/MM/DD
after:YYY/MM/DD
tag:tag-name



----

example: a single message

	https://groups.google.com/d/msg/spaghettiopendata/58Wfrxw-KrI/LaBagYeD4pcJ


example: searching between tow dates, with a tag

	https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topicsearchin/spaghettiopendata/before$3A2012$2F08$2F22$20after$3A2012$2F07$2F22$20tag$3Atwitter
	
then select a topic

	https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topicsearchin/spaghettiopendata/before$3A2012$2F08$2F22$20after$3A2012$2F07$2F22$20/spaghettiopendata/58Wfrxw-KrI
	
NOTE: once selected, the topic will add its sub-path to the previous url
NOTE: in the url for search the tag name:value are concatenated and url-encoded, with a `$` char in place of the usual `%` symbol.


